docs.name: Saibo Co., Ltd. (3123)
docs.description: Saibo Co., Ltd. is mainly engaged in the manufacture and sale of textile products. The Textile segment manufactures and sells knit products, uniforms, clothing, promoting products, rayon yarns, synthetic yarns, hemp fabrics, and embroidery lace. The Commercial Facility Leasing segment is mainly engaged in the leasing of commercial facilities. The Golf Ranges segment operates golf ranges. The Others segment is involved in the leasing of other real estate except commercial facilities, the maintenance of buildings, the painting and repair of automotive steel plates, the quid pro quo sale for ceremonial occasions, the sale and rental of automatic water supply for flower pots, the operation of car training centers, the construction of interiors, as well as the operation of Toyota motor sales agency. As of March 31, 2012, it had five subsidiaries and three associated companies. On April 1, 2013, it sold automobile sheet-metal painting and repair business to a Japan-based company.

docs.name: Koeln-Duesseldorfer D.Rheinschiffahrt AG (KDR)
docs.description: Koeln Duesseldorfer Deutsche Rheinschiffahrt AG operates a cruise line on the Rhine River in Germany. The Company offers various leisure activities, such as the Firework Cruises, Party Cruises, Sundays On KD, Dinner Shows, Round-trip Cruises as well as regular scheduled cruises. The Company also provides special cruises for the mother's day, father's day, as well as other special theme parties and show events. In addition, Koeln Duesseldorfer Deutsche Rheinschiffahrt AG offers charter services for different occasions, such as weddings, birthdays, conferences, cultural and other social events. For all events, the Company offers its own catering services, which provide a range of culinary options. The Company operates two business segments: day boat trips and ship management services, which encompasses the ship management services performed by its wholly owned KD Bereederung GmbH & Co. KG

docs.name: PMDAX: Principal Funds Inc. Small-Mid
docs.description:
The investment seeks to provide a relatively high level of current income and long-term growth of income, and secondarily long-term growth of capital, while investing primarily in small- to mid-capitalization companies.
 Under normal circumstances, the fund invests at least 80% of its net assets, plus borrowings for investment purposes, in dividend-paying equity securities of companies with small to medium market capitalizations at the time of purchase. It will invest in the securities of foreign issuers, real estate investment trusts, preferred securities, convertible securities, fixed-income securities, master limited partnerships, and royalty trusts.

docs.name: Super Group Limited (SPG)
docs.description: Super Group Limited is a holding company. It is engaged in supply chain management business, operating in South Africa, with operations across Sub-Saharan Africa and businesses in Australia, New Zealand and the United Kingdom. Its operating activities include supply chain management, dealerships and fleet management activities. Its operating segments include Super Group, Supply Chain, Supply Chain South Africa, African Logistics, Fleet Solutions, FleetAfrica, SG Fleet and Dealerships. Its services include transportation, warehousing, primary distribution, secondary distribution, supply chain consulting, supply chain technologies, network design, international forwarding and clearing, customs brokerage, cross border transport, vehicle rental, outsourced fleet management and new and used car sales and service.

docs.name: PMIMX: Putnam Michigan Tax Exempt Inco
docs.description:
